ative Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."]},{"name":"Robers","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."]},{"name":"Roberds","meanings":["English: variant of   Roberts  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Robards","meanings":["English (Kent): variant of   Roberts  ."]},{"name":"Robarts","meanings":["English (Bedfordshire and Hertfortshire): variant of   Roberts  ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Lavedre","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jorge, Juan, Manuel, Adriana, Alvaro, Bernardo, Elena, Ezequiel, Francisca, Francisco, Jaime, Liliana.  Italian Dario, Leonardo, Salvatore.","Spanish; Italian (mainly <b>La Verde</b>): variant of   Verde   ‘green’, with (fused) definite article <i>la</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Verde","meanings":["Reduced form of   Gertrud ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Robertus de Lavedre was born in 1158, in Scotland as the son of Joanni Lavder. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"1158–":"1158–Surnud","1158–Male":"1158–Surnud","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1123–Male":"1123–Surnud","1190":"1190","1158":"1158","1123":"1123","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"1158–":"1158–Kuollut","1158–Male":"1158–Kuollut","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1123–Male":"1123–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1158":"1158","1123":"1123","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"1158–":"1158–Décédé","1158–Male":"1158–Décédé","1190–Male":"1190–Décédé","1123–Male":"1123–Décédé","1190":"1190","1158":"1158","1123":"1123","Scotland":"Écosse","lifeSummary":"Robertus de Lavedre est né en 1158, à Écosse, fils de Joanni Lavder. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1158–":"1158–Verstorben","1158–Male":"1158–Verstorben","1190–Male":"1190–Verstorben","1123–Male":"1123–Verstorben","1190":"1190","1158":"1158","1123":"1123","Scotland":"Scotland","lifeSummary":"Robertus de Lavedre wurde 1158 in Scotland, als Sohn von Joanni Lavder geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1158–":"1158–Desede","1158–Male":"1158–Desede","1190–Male":"1190–Desede","1123–Male":"1123–Desede","1190":"1190","1158":"1158","1123":"1123","Scotland":"Scotland"},"hu":{"1158–":"1158–elhunyt","1158–Male":"1158–elhunyt","1190–Male":"1190–elhunyt","1123–Male":"1123–elhunyt","1190":"1190","1158":"1158","1123":"1123","Scotland":"Scotland"},"id":{"1158–":"1158–Telah Meninggal","1158–Male":"1158–TelahMeninggal","1190–Male":"1190–Telah Meninggal","1123–Male":"1123–Telah Meninggal","1190":"1190","1158":"1158","1123":"